# AVISEP

AVISEP is an evaluation system of courses and modules, dedicated to ISEP.
It should be used to improve the way teachers organize their courses and how to present them.

## Local Deployement

AVISEP is a Dynamic Web Project that works perfectly on Spring Tool Suite

1. Download Zip or Clone the git repository.
2. Import as a Maven Existing Project in Spring Tool Suite
3. Create a database called 'avisepdb' in your favourite SQL manager (default : MySQL)
4. Set your properties in the 'application.properties' file (spring.datasource.username, spring.datasource.password and spring.datasource.url)
5. Right click on the avisep file in STS, then Run As > Spring Boot App.
6. Go on localhost:8080 and it should work !

## Back-End

Only Java language, with Spring framework.

## Front-End

Basic front, including jQuery, Bootstrap and Ajax.
It contains :
1. A login page
2. 3 'Welcome' pages, depending on the role of the user that will be logged in.
3. A 'Create Form' page, which is the form builder.
4. A 'Answer Form' page, which is where the form created by a teacher for a specific course or module will be displayed to students who are registered in this one.
5. A "View Results' page, which is made for teachers, to consult students' answers for each form.

